title: Ref #38. Implemented remove and added into demo app. Added convenience method to…
message: Ref #38. Implemented remove and added into demo app. Added convenience method to instantiate internal maps in response to a bug fix whereby filtering map didn't create the correct type of map. Child2Group cache is now a WeakReferencedMap. Should help reduce leaking due to a child key no longer having the same hashcode. Would happen if object was changed outside of adapter. Fixed bug where areGroupsSorted would get overriden but not reflect the change. Minor documentation adjustments.

title: Ref #42. Solved, CAB not restoring during config changes. Was trying to avoid…
message: Ref #42. Solved, CAB not restoring during config changes. Was trying to avoid it, but made ExpandableListView a required parameter for instantiation of the RolodexAdapter instead of obtaining during getGroupView(). Also dropped Context param during init and moved context storing to the BaseRolodexAdapter.

title: Ref #42. Moved a lot of the core functionality needed for all upcoming Rolodex…
message: Ref #42. Moved a lot of the core functionality needed for all upcoming Rolodex adapters to a BaseRolodexAdapter class. This includes collapse/expand All methods, selectable methods, stableIds, and the getView methods. Looks like modal setChoice is working. Implemented a solution within the BaseRolodexAdapter which takes over alot of the callbacks and interaction with ListView methods. Needs more testing yet. Updated demo classes to use the new behavior.

title: Ref #25 - Overhauled JSONArray adapter's filtering design. On adapter…
message: Ref #25 - Overhauled JSONArray adapter's filtering design. On adapter initialization, caches all methods which match the isFilteredBy method signature. During a filtering operation, which isFilteredBy to reflexively invoke is determined by the object type pulled from JSONArray. If no matching method, default Object type is used.

Includes a new package with activity, frag, and movie adapter.  Added header ability to main/root activity.  Renamed a lot of the classes since some of their names were getting too long. MovieItem supports a toString() method...required to support Android ArrayAdapter's built in ArrayFilter.
